author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
Medicaid began as a welfare program, but 60 years later it covers one in five Americans and costs more than $800 billion. But Trump’s “Big Beautiful Bill” is changing the health insurance program. 

WSJ explores how Medicaid got so big and how the GOP megabill will change it.
